{"TopicId":218902,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"Better radial decoupler snap indicator","CreatedByName":"cocoscacao","CreatedById":225696,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-15T15:10:25Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"cocoscacao","CreatedById":225696,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-15T15:10:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen placing boosters, or anything to radial decouplers, especially the smaller ones, it is sometimes hard to discern whether the part will be placed on them or not. Make decouplers glow yellow or something, to indicate where the part will end up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-15T15:12:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s the main reason why blueprint view exists.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-08-15T15:12:48Z\u0022 title=\u002208/15/2023 03:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Aug 15\u0022\u003EAugust 15, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by The Aziz\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cocoscacao","CreatedById":225696,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-15T20:52:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224312675\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218902\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221692112358\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s the main reason why blueprint view exists.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s very useful for checking angles and center of mass/thrust, but I still think it would be a nice QOL feature to know where the parts will be placed (attached), while they\u0027re being placed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-08-15T20:53:04Z\u0022 title=\u002208/15/2023 08:53  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Aug 15\u0022\u003EAugust 15, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by cocoscacao\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}